     Boulogne-sur-Mer - Interest in exhibition of Slovak
glass-artists in France, opened in June 1996, was enormous. By
September, more than 14,000 visitors have come to see the
exhibition. This is a record attendance, when taking all summer
exhibitions into consideration, said Francoise Poiret, curator
of the Musee Chateau Boulogne-sur-Mer.

     Bratislava - The Slovak parliament continues its 17th
session on Wednesday with a discussion on the governmental bill
on prosecution.

      Bratislava - The fifth congress of the European
Association of Gynecological Endoscopy began in Bratislava, on
Wednesday. It its for the first time, when an event of a similar
significance in this field of medicine, will take place in
Slovakia, or in former Czecho-Slovakia, at all. 
    
    Novy Cas: New Kocnars 
      Bratislava - According to the latest events, the
disintegration of Association of Slovak Workers (ZRS) progressed
to the next chapter. After the establishment of the United
Worker's Party of Slovakia (ZRSS) by Mazar (adviser to ZRS
Chairman Jan Luptak) and Kocnar (Luptak's former colleague),
this disintegration moved to the parliament as well. On Tuesday
September 17th two ZRS deputies, Kolnik and Poliak, announced
their departure at the ZRS Club session.

      Bratislava - The members of the Coordination Committee for
Women's Issues returned from the international conference
entitled "Implementation of Action Platform in Central and
Eastern European Countries." The conference took place between
September 12-14 in the Romanian capital Bucharest.

      Bratislava - Parliamentary Chairman Ivan Gasparovic
received Arpad Bogsch, Director General of the World
Intellectual Property Organization (WIPO), in Bratislava on
Wednesday. During the meeting Gasparovic informed his guest
about the activities of the Slovak parliament and the process of
transformation in Slovak society and economy. 

    Pravda: Trade Unions' Flag in the Wind
      Bratislava - Leaders of KOVO, the largest Slovak trade
union, make no bones about their plans to withhold support for
the candidature of the Confederation of Trade Unions's (KOZ)
leadership for continued tenure at the KOZ congress in October.
The cause is sustained discontent over the current state of the
central body of trade unions. Eugen Skultety, Vice-Chairman of
KOVO, nominated for the post of the KOZ Vice-President,
clarified the main reasons (for their displeasure). "In our eyes
the Confederation is acting like a flag in the wind. For more
than two years we've been pointing to the shortcomings in its
performance. However, we are well-aware that that is not
enough," The reality, acknowledged by KOVO members, is simply
that the country's trade unions of today are not a real force,
one that could express as well as carry out their views.

      Bratislava - Ivan Simko, Christian-Democratic Movement
deputy, announced during the 17th session of the Slovak
Parliament on Wednesday, that a group of 36 deputies have
submitted a new proposal to the parliament to discuss the
no-confidence vote in Ivan Hudec, the Minister of Culture, next
parliamentary session summoned immediately after the on-going
session.

      Medzev, September 18, (SLOVAKIA) - An international
seminar devoted to the research, preservation, and use of caves
that have been made accessible (for public viewing), began in
Medzev, the district of Kosice-Surroundings on Wednesday.

      Bratislava - Slovak Premier Vladimir Meciar received Betty
Boothroyd, Speaker of the British House of Commons, in
Bratislava, on Wednesday.

      Bratislava - Slovak Culture Minister Ivan Hudec presented
three distinguished personalities, Drahoslav Machala, Dusan
Caplovic and Jan Brtek, with the Honor of Culture Minister award
on Wedneday.

      Brno - Slovakia has its National Day on Wednesday at the
38th International Engineering Fair in Brno. It was opened by
Slovak Economy Minister Karol Cesnek. In his speech Cesnek said
that the engineering industry has an important position in the
Slovak economy. In 1995, its portion increased to 17.7 per cent
and continues to increase in 1996. Cesnek stressed that Slovak
exhibitors traditionally visit the Brno fair. In 1996, along
with Germany, Slovakia is the largest foreign exhibitor with 118
participants and 3,900 square meters of exhibition space.

       Bratislava- Slovak Premier Vladimir Meciar received Polish
Foreign Affairs Ministry Dariusz Rosati on Wednesday in
Bratislava. After the meeting, Rosati said that it is in the
interest of Poland and Slovakia, as well as other central
European countries, to become members of European Union (EU) and
NATO. He said that in addition to illustrating mutual support,
it is necessary to fulfill all the conditions required by these
Euro-Atlantic structures. 

       Bratislava - Slovak Premier Vladimir Meciar received
Turkish Ambassador to Slovakia Aydin Sahinbas at the conclusion
of his diplomatic mission.

       Bratislava - Slovak Minister of Transportation, Postal
Services, and Telecommunications Alexander Rezes's pacemaker
will soon be changed, Cardiovascular Surgery Clinic (UKVCH)
Director Viliam Fischer told Slovakia. He, at the same time,
refuted the Novy Cas daily information indicating that Rezes's
cardiovascular disorder calls for complicated heart surgery.

       Budapest - An official meeting of Slovak and Hungarian
premiers, Vladimir Meciar and Gyula Horn and parliamentary
chairs Ivan Gasparovic and Zoltan Gal will be held this year in
Slovakia.

       Banska Bystrica - General Director of World Intellectual
Property Organization (WIPO) Arpad Bogsch, on Wednesday, took
over a honorary doctorate at the Matej Bel University' (UBM) Law
School. Constitutional Court Chair Milan Cic and other state
administration representatives attended.

       Bratislava - The 4th international conference of
architects called DOCOMOMO International was kicked off in
Bratislava on Wednesday. The participants are scheduled to visit
objects built in functionalistic style and located at various
places in Slovakia - - in Sliac, Svit, Vysne Hagy, Piestany and
Bratislava. The event is attended by 180 participants from more
than 30 countries.

       Bratislava - The British House of Commons Speaker Betty
Boothroyd concluded her four-day visit to Slovakia on Wednesday.

       Bratislava - A press conference at the Slovak National
Gallery (SNG) provided information on Slovak architects'
participation in the 4th International Architecture Exhibition
in Venezia, Italy, being held from September 15 to November 16.

       Kosice - Juh Kosice District Mayor Jaroslav Hlinka served
more than 500 civil marriages but he will have to repeat the
Wednesday's wedding ceremony during which Maria Horvathova and
Marian Zlamal from Kosice said their Yes. As he told SLOVAKIA
correspondent the repetition will be held over the Atlantic on
September 19 on a plane via Vienna-New York. By this act a
life-dream nourished by Zlamal family will be fulfilled thanks
to the Slovak TV show Let's Dream With Us.

       Banska Bystrica - Branislav Petroch, the Director of the
Agrobanka's Banska Bystrica- headquartered branch office, told
SLOVAKIA that the Czech National Bank (CNB) will provide a full
guarantee for Agrobanka (AGB) clients in the Czech Republic and
Slovakia.
      The move is in response to the CNB's decision on temporary
receivership for the Prague-headquartered AGB, currently the
fifth largest financial house in the Czech Republic, prompted by
an investigation of the collapse of the Credit Bank a.s.,
headquartered in Plzen, the Czech Republic.

       Bratislava - With the participation of Ivan Hudec Culture
Minister, the premiere of the 30 minutes documentary on Jozef
Ciger-Hronsky, a Slovak writer, took place at the Koliba a.s.
Bratislava studio. The documentary's director is Ivan
Petrovicky.
       Bratislava - The Dutch insurance company
Nationale-Nederlanden a.s., daughter company of ING Group,
entered the Slovak insurance market on Wednesday.
      At a press conference, the general director of the Slovak
branch Ed Teer told journalists that 25 experts and 150 agents
will work at the branch covering all of Slovakia -- the only
central and east European country without a
Nationale-Nederlanden branch.

      Bratislava - Several computer servers in Slovakia connected
to the Internet network were under attack this week by a hacker
group called Syrup Emergency Response Team (SERT). The hackers
erased all illegal software from the servers and installed 
documents promoting fight against software piracy.	

      Bratislava - Ladislav Slobodnik, Head of the Slovak
Environment Ministry Office, received a World Bank Mission led
by its senior expert for the environment and economy Helmut
Schreiber.
     The mission is a preparation of the Slovak delegation's
participation in the World Bank General Assembly and World
Environment Fund. Slovak Finance Minister Sergej Kozlik will
lead the Slovak mission.

      Budapest - Slovak Foreign Minister Pavol Hamzik said his
negotiations in Hungary, the first since his installment as
minister, were very open and valuable. He paid a one-day visit
to Budapest on Wednesday.
     Hamzik and his Hungarian counterpart Laszlo Kovacs
discussed aspects of European and trans-Atlantic integration.
Kovacs stressed mutual support for integration efforts, Hamzik
said. "The basic thing is that both sides are interested in
settling controversial issues. We don't like to be pressured,
but we know very well that the European Union welcomes any
mutual progress," Hamzik said, adding that regarding this staff
there is much room for improvement.

    Bratislava 18. septembra (TASR) - Misiu Svetovej banky
vedenu Helmutom Schreiberom - starsim expertom pre zivotne
prostredie a ekonomiku - prijal dnes v Bratislave veduci uradu
Ministerstva zivotneho prostredia SR Ladislav Slobodnik.
    Misia je pripravou ucasti slovenskej delegacie vedenej
podpredsedom vlady SR a ministrom financii SR Sergejom Kozlikom
na generalnej rade Svetovej banky (SB) a Svetoveho fondu
zivotneho prostredia (GEF).
     Prerokovali projekty z oblasti zivotneho prostredia, ktore
by mohli byt spolufinancovane Svetovou bankou - najma vyuzivanie
geotermalnej energie, vytvorenie obratoveho fondu zivotneho
prostredia, podporu mimovladnych organizacii, investovanie do
ochrany povodi a jednotlivych zloziek zivotneho prostredia.
    TASR informovala dnes hovorkyna MZP SR Yvonne Holla.

    Bratislava 18. septembra (TASR) - Delegaciu vyboru pre
obranu nemeckeho Spolkoveho snemu - Bundestagu vedenu jeho
predsedom Klausom Rosem prijal dnes podvecer v Bratislave
riaditel sekcie obrany a bezpecnosti Uradu vlady SR plukovnik
Frantisek Blanarik.
    Predmetom rozhovoru boli otazky systemu zabezpecenia a
pripravy statu na obranu, ulohy, ktore plni Rada obrany statu,
jej zlozenie, ako aj zabezpecovanie cinnosti a priprava
jednotlivych regionov na obranu. F. Blanarik zdoraznil, ze pre
mladu Slovensku republiku su informacie okolitych statov z
oblasti riadenia, systemu ich obrany, ochrany, bezpecnosti aj
planovania velmi dolezite na skvalitnovanie prace institucii
zaoberajucich sa touto problematikou.
    Delegacia Bundestagu si potom prezrela historicke objekty
bratislavskeho Stareho Mesta.
    Zajtra nemeckych hosti prijme predseda vlady SR Vladimir
Meciar, navstivia Generalny stab Armady SR v Trencine, kde sa
stretnu s jeho nacelnikom generalplukovnikom Jozefom Tuchynom a
zavitaju aj do Vojenskeho utvaru v Nitre, specializujuceho sa na
pripravu slovenskych vojakov vysielanych do mierovych misii OSN.

snemovne britskeho parlamentu Betty Boothroydova ukoncila dnes v
Bratislave stvordnovu navstevu Slovenskej republiky.
    Na hranicnom priechode v Bratislave-Bergu sa s nou rozlucili

    NNNN     A. Bogsch prvym cestnym doktorom UMB     A. Bogsch prvym cestnym doktorom UMB
    
    Banska Bystrica 18. septembra (TASR) - Generalny riaditel
Svetovej organizacie dusevneho vlastnictva (WIPO) Arpad Bogsch
dnes prevzal cestny doktorat pravnych vied na Pravnickej fakulte
Univerzity Mateja Bela (PF UMB) v Banskej Bystrici. Stalo sa tak
na slavnostnom zasadnuti Vedeckej rady UMB, rozsirenom o vedecke
rady siedmich fakult, na ktorom sa zucastnil predseda Ustavneho
sudu SR Milan Cic, predstavitelia statnej spravy a samospravy,
ako aj dalsi hostia.
    Vedecku hodnost dr.h.c. udelila Pravnicka fakulta UMB A.
Bogschovi vzhladom na jeho prinos do teorie a praxe najma v
oblasti medzinarodnej ochrany dusevneho vlastnictva. Generalny
riaditel WIPO ma vysoke zasluhy na bezproblemovej sukcesii
ceskeho a slovenskeho Uradu priemysloveho vlastnictva v
medzinarodnych dohodach a zmluvach suvisiacich s ochranou
dusevneho vlastnictva.
    Cestnym doktoratom ocenili celozivotnu pracu A. Bogscha v
oblasti ochrany dusevneho vlastnictva a pomoc, ktoru preukazal
Slovenskej republike. Generalny riaditel WIPO sa tak stal prvym
doktorom honoris causa banskobystrickej univerzity, ktora sa
konstituovala pred styrmi rokmi. Rektor UMB Otto Tomecek oznacil
tuto udalost za velmi vyznamnu, pretoze univerzita, patriaca
medzi najvyznamnejsie institucie na strednom Slovensku, sa tym
zaradila medzi vyznamne svetove univerzity, ktore udelili A.
Bogschovi cestny doktorat.
    
    Jozef Habocik na
    NNNN     O slovenskej ucasti na vystave v Benatkach     O slovenskej ucasti na vystave v Benatkach
    
    Bratislava 18. septembra (TASR) -  O slovenskej ucasti na
VI. medzinarodnej vystave architektury v Benatkach, ktora sa
kona od 15. septembra do 16. novembra, informovali dnes
novinarov na tlacovej besede v Slovenskej narodnej galerii v
Bratislave.
    Ako povedala narodna komisarka vystavy Henrieta Moravcikova,
prezentuje sa na nej 32 narodnych expozicii najroznejsimi
architektonickymi projektmi vratane nestandardnych, radikalnych
aj varujucich. Ceny - Benatskych zlatych levov ziskal americky
architekt Philip Johnson, Ignazio Gardella z Talianska a Oscar
Niemayer z Brazilie. Dalsich troch Zlatych levov udelili
autorom, ktori najlepsie interpretovali temu - architekt ako
seizmograf. Ziskali ich autori z Francuzska, Spanielska a
skupina mladych finskych architektov. Ako najlepsiu narodnu
reprezentaciu ocenili japonsky pavilon.
    Slovensku republiku prezentuje na vystave velky model
kostolika vo Vojkovciach, okres Spisska Nova Ves, v mierke 1:10.
Velkoplosne fotografie a texty priblizuju navstevnikom pribeh
jehho vzniku. Obyvatelia Vojkoviec sa usilovali o jeho vystavbu
od sestdesiatych rokov a vybudovali ho z vlastnych zdrojov v
spolupraci s architektom a vytvarnikmi po revolucnych zmenach v
novembri 1989. Stavba netradicneho kostolika v tvare rotundy s
malymi okruhlymi oknami posobi zaujimavym dojmom. Po skonceni
vystavy v Benatkach maju expoziciu instalovat v Bratislave.
    Riaditel SNG Juraj Zary dodal, ze slovenska expozicia je
vhodne realizovana v priestoroch spolocneho Cesko-Slovenskeho
pavilonu v Benatkach. Je dostatocne velky na to, aby sa v nom
mohli prezentovat obe krajiny. Doteraz vsak nie je doriesene
rozdelenie tohto spolocneho majetku. Preto bude SNG apelovat na
Ministerstvo kultury SR, aby vyvinulo snahu vyriesit tento
problem. Bola by totiz velka skoda prist o takuto vyznamnu
moznost prezentacie slovenskej kultury v zahranici.
    
    Carmen Cupalova na
    NNNN    Ministrovi A.Rezesovi vymenia kardiostimulator    Ministrovi A.Rezesovi vymenia kardiostimulator
    
    Bratislava 18. septembra (TASR) - Ministrovi dopravy, post a
telekomunikacii SR Alexandrovi Rezesovi v najblizsich dnoch
vymenia kardiostimulator. Informaciu dnes TASR poskytol
prednosta Kliniky kardiovaskularnej chirurgie UKVCH na
Partizanskej ulici v Bratislave doc. MUDr. Viliam Fischer CSc.,
kde je pacient od vcera hospitalizovany. Zaroven vyvratil dnesnu
informaciu dennika Novy cas, ze minister ma vazne srdcovo-cievne
problemy vyzadujuce si komplikovanu operaciu tepny a srdca.
    Doc. V. Fischer povedal, ze pripad A. Rezesa mozno povazovat
v medicinskej praxi za unikatny, pretoze jeho kardiostimulator,
ktory sice dalej funguje, stratil schopnost davat informacie.
Stalo sa to po tom, ked minister pocas dovolenky presiel na
colnici cez ramovy detektor kovov, ktory narusil cinnost
"strojceka". Podla statistik sa takato udalost vyskytuje u dvoch
z desattisic pacientov s kardiostimulatorom.
    Podla sefa kardiochirurgie raritou je aj to, ze cinnost
kardiostimulatora sa sice narusila, ale na druhej strane doslo k
zlepseniu funkcie a vykonnosti lavej srdcovej komory ministra.
    Doc. V. Fischer konstatoval, ze vymena kardiostimulatora nie
je narocny vykon na srdci. Ide iba o 10 az 15-minutovu podkoznu
operaciu, po ktorej moze pacient na druhy den opustit operaciu.

    NNNN     Zo stretnutia u predsedu NR SR     Zo stretnutia u predsedu NR SR
    
    Bratislava 18.septembra (TASR) - Predseda Narodnej rady SR
Ivan Gasparovic prijal dnes v Bratislave ministra zahranicnych
veci Polskej republiky Dariusza Rosatiho. Na brifingu po
skonceni rozhovorov obaja politici zdoraznili, ze hovorili spolu
predovsetkym o otazkach europskej integracie a moznostiach
spoluprace oboch krajin pri zaclenovani sa do bezpecnostnych a
hospodarskych struktur kontinentu.
    Sef polskej diplomacie za vyznamu povazuje diskusiu ako
mozno zvysit sance Polska i Slovenska na urychleny vstup do
Europskej unie a NATO. Obaja sa zhodli na tom, ze Ruska
federacia - odhliadnuc od nasich integracnych snah - zostane pre
obidve krajiny dolezitym partnerom. D.Rosati je presvedceny, ze
Rusko sa musi podielat na konstrukcii bezpecnosti Europy.
    I.Gasparovic zdoraznil, ze diskutovali o problemoch, ktore
region stednej Europy potrebuje riesit. Ide o mnohostrannu
spolupracu, ale aj bilateralne kontakty. Integraciu oboch krajin
do europskych a transatlantickych struktur oznacil za predpoklad
politickej stability a hospodarskeho rozvoja. Za dolezite pri
realizacii tychto snah povazuje stretnutia exekutivy i
predstavitelov parlamentov. "Kazdy musi sam riesit problemy,
ktore vyplyvaju z Bielej knihy EU. Pokial sme na rovnakej
startovacej ciare a urovni v plneni uloh a povinnosti, potom je
vzajomna podpora opodstatnena a musi byt jednoznacna. O tom sme
sa vzajomne ubezpecili", dodal predseda parlamentu.

    Bratislava 18. septembra (TASR) - Predseda vlady SR Vladimir
Meciar prijal dnes v Bratislave predsednicku Dolnej komory
britskeho parlamentu Betty Boothroydovu.
    Ako po stretnuti B. Boothroydova zdoraznila, rozhovor sa
tykal najma otazok suvisiacich so vstupom SR do NATO a Europskej
unie, pricom ocenila vzajomnu otvorenost. Hovorkyna slovenskeho
premiera Magda Pospisilova informovala, ze V. Meciar oznacil
navstevu britskej politicky za dokaz pokracovania
britsko-slovenskych kontaktov a potvrdil jednoznacne smerovanie
Slovenskej republiky do EU a NATO. Informoval B. Boothroydovu,
ze SR je pripravena splnit do roku 1998 podmienky na zacatie
rozhovorov o vstupe do EU, pricom nevylucil aj skorsie splnenie
kriterii. Potvrdil takisto plnenie zavazkov SR vyplyvajuce z
nasho usilia o vstup do NATO. Zaroven zdoraznil aj globalne
zaujmy, ktore v tejto otazke maju svoj vyznam.
    B. Boothroydova ocenila ucast premiera a celej vlady na jej
utornajsom vystupeni v Narodnej rade SR. Pocas rozhovoru
prejavila zaujem aj o zlozenie parlamentnych organov. V. Meciar
konstatoval, ze opozicia je zastupena v kazdom vybore, len nema
predsedov a podpredsedov vyborov. Premier poukazal na uspechy SR
v ekonomike a za urcite nase nevyhody oznacil fakt, ze
rozdelenie Cesko-Slovenska bolo vnimane v zahranici casto
negativne, ako aj internacionalizaciu vnutornych problemov.

otec A.Bogscha sa narodil v Kezmarku. Premier zdoraznil, ze WIPO
sa zaobera tym najperspektivnejsim artiklom - bohatstvom
dusevneho vlastnictva a hostovi sa podakoval za pomoc pri
priprave nasich odbornikov a pri zakladani Uradu priemyselneho
vlastnictva SR (UPV SR). V.Meciar vyhlasil, ze tento urad musi
zabezpecovat nielen ochranu dusevneho vlastnictva, ale aj
propagaciu nasich poznatkov vo svete.
    A.Bogsch na pressfoyer uviedol, ze taziskom jeho sucasnej
navstevy Slovenska je ucast na oficialnom otvoreni UPV v Banskej
Bystrici. Ocenil pokrok, ktory Slovenska republika dosiahla pri
budovani tohto uradu od ziskania statnej nezavislosti v roku
1993. Zdoraznil, ze WIPO zdruzuje takmer vsetky staty sveta a
jej ulohou je ochrana dusevneho vlastnictva a autorskych prav,
ako aj pomoc novym clenom pri uprave prislusnej legislativy.

	    NNNN     Hackeri napadli slovenske pocitace na sieti Internet     Hackeri napadli slovenske pocitace na sieti Internet

    Niekolko slovenskych pocitacov a serverov napojenych na
sieti Internet bolo tento tyzden tercom utokov skupiny hackerov, 
nazyvanych Syrup Emergency Reaction Team (SERT). Dovodom ich utoku 
bolo upozornit na rozmach zneuzivania Internetu na rozsirovanie 
kradnuteho licencneho softwaru.
 
    Medzi napadnutymi pocitacmi boli aj servery firiem zaoberajucimi 
sa poskytovanim sluzieb suvisiacichs pripojenim k sieti Internet, 
ako napriklad Slovak Academic Network (SANET), alebo Netlab s.r.o.,
ale aj mnoho skolskych servrov, o ktorych je zname ze su zneuzivane 
na distribuciu nelegalneho softwaru. Na napadnutych serveroch bol 
vymazany vsetok najdeny nelegalny software a boli na nich
instalovane propagacne stranky povzbudzujuce k boju proti sireniu 
kradnuteho softwaru.

	    NNNN     Slovnaft, a.s. uvazuje o zvyseni ceny nafty a benzinu BA 98     Slovnaft, a.s. uvazuje o zvyseni ceny nafty a benzinu BA 98
    
    Bratislava 18. septembra (TASR) -  Slovnaft, a. s,
Bratislava "uvazuje o tom, ze poda ministerstvu financii navrh
na zvysenie ceny motorovej nafty o 10 halierov a benzinu BA 98,
teda pohonnej latky, ktora ma najvyssiu oktanovu hladinu. Je to
najma z toho dovodu, ze existuje uzky cenovy diafazon medzi
cenovou hladinou benzinu BA 91 a BA 98", uviedol v dnesnej
vecernej relacii STV Noviny v suvislosti so zvysenim ceny
jedneho litra nafty v Ceskej republike o 50 halierov predseda
Predstavenstva a generalny riaditel akciovej spolocnosti
Slovnaft Slavomir Hatina.
    Ako dalej v relacii odznelo, pripadne zvysenie ceny benzinu
BA 98 o 40 halierov by nemali pocitit bezni motoristi, kedze
tento benzin pouzivaju len luxusne vozidla. Dovodom rozhodnutia
Slovnaftu, a.s. navrhnut zvysenie cien niektorych pohonnych
latok od 1. oktobra 1996 je najma dramaticky rast cien ropy na
svetovych trhoch v septembri. "V sucasnosti sa jej cenova
hladina pohybuje na urovni medzi 22,5 az 25 USD za barel, co je
najvyssia cena od kuvajtskej krizy v roku 1991", dodal S.
Hatina.
    Cerpacie stanice Slovnaftu, a.s. v Bratislave v sucasnosti
predavaju liter benzinu Natural BA 98 za 21,90 Sk a motorovej
nafty za 19,30 Sk.
    Monika Durcenkova ga
    * * *  Prehlbenie spoluprace medzi VSZ Kosice a Trineckymi zelezarnami  Prehlbenie spoluprace medzi VSZ Kosice a Trineckymi zelezarnami
    
    Bratislava 18. septembra (TASR) - Dohodou o moznosti
buduceho kapitaloveho prepojenia VSZ, a. s. Kosice a Trineckych
zelezaren, a. s., sa skoncilo dnesne rokovanie predstavitelov
oboch spolocnosti v ramci 38. Medzinarodneho strojarskeho
veltrhu v Brne.
    Ako TASR informovali predseda Predstavenstva VSZ, a. s.
Kosice Jan Smerek a predseda Predstavenstva Trineckych zelezaren
a. s. Rudolf Ovcari, prehlbenie uz zacatej spoluprace VSZ, a. s.
Kosice a Trineckych zelezaren, a. s., ma jediny ciel - posilnit
sucasne pozicie oboch hut na europskych trhoch. V pripade
kapitaloveho prepojenia by podiel VSZ a. s. Kosice v Trineckych
zelezarnach, a. s., neprekrocil 20 percent. Rokovalo sa i o
reciprocnom nakupe akcii VSZ  Trineckymi zelezarnami, a.s. v
objeme do 10 percent.
    V ramci tychto aktivit sa zacnu obchodne rokovania VSZ a
Trineckych zelezaren s jednym z najvacsich polskych hutnickych
podnikov Huta Katowice.
    Tieto kroky su pokracovanim uz zacatej obchodnej spoluprace
a maju za ciel integraciu hutnickych podnikov v stredoeuropskom
regione.
    dh ga
    * * *     Riaditel B. Petroch o situacii v Agrobanke     Riaditel B. Petroch o situacii v Agrobanke
    
    Banska Bystrica 18. septembra (TASR) - Ceska narodna banka v
suvislosti so vysetrovanim krachu Kreditnej banky, a. s. Plzen
rozhodla o uvaleni docasnej nutenej spravy Agrobanky, a. s.
(AGB) Praha, ktory je v sucasnosti piaty najvacsi penazny ustav
v Ceskej republike.
    Bilancna suma AGB Praha predstavuje podla slovenskeho
riaditela jej zahranicnej pobocky so sidlom v Banskej Bystrici
Branislava Petrocha, v prepocte 70 miliard Sk a vklady 50
miliard Sk. Podla neho pre vsetkych klientov AGB v SR i CR plati
neodvolatelna zaruka CNB pre akykolvek objem prostriedkov.
    Za jeden a pol dna (od 17. septembra) klienti AGB na
Slovensku vybrali hotovostne aj bezhotovostne vklady za 150
milionov Sk a vcera vlozili vklady vo vyske 10 milionov Sk.
"Agrobanka je likvidna, ma dostatocnu penaznu zasobu nad ramec
beznych financnych obratov. Zahranicna pobocka AGB v Banskej
Bystrici zabezpecuje beznu prevadzku a je schopna uspokojovat
akekolvek poziadavky klientov."
    Potvrdil, ze zahranicna pobocka AGB v Banskej Bystrici s
bilancnou sumou 4,5 miliardy Sk je v sucasnosti v transformacnom
procese.
    Upozornil, ze AGB Praha uvazuje zo slovenskej pobocky
vytvorit dcersku spolocnost so zakladnym imanim jedna miliarda
Sk, pricom slovenske mimobankove subjekty sa budu podielat na
kapitali dcery dvoma tretinami.
    Helena Kulova, Danica Kubisova dh ga
    * * *     O slovensko-lotysskych privatizacnych vztahoch     O slovensko-lotysskych privatizacnych vztahoch
    
    Bratislava 18. septembra (TASR) - Rozpad sovietskeho imperia
vyrazne poznacil ekonomicke vazby Lotysska s krajinami byvaleho
Sovietskeho zvazu. Aj to je dovod, preco Lotyssko hlada v
suvislosti s ekonomickou transformaciou kontakty so zahranicnymi
partnermi. Na dnesnom slovensko-lotysskom rokovani o
privatizacii v zahranici to povedal T. Linkaits. Zdorazil, ze
privatizaciu v Lotyssku vyrazne ovplyvnuju aj zmeny v podobe
novelizacii znacneho poctu zakonov. Tie vsak zahranicnych
investorov nediskriminuju.
    T. Linkaits potvrdil, ze privatizacia v oblasti drevarskej
vyroby sa v Lotyssku skoncila a Lotysska privatizacna agentura
ma za ulohu zabezpecit do konca roka privatizaciu 75 percent z
celkoveho poctu statnych podnikov.
    V krajine pouzivaju aj privatizacnu metodu prostrednictvom
certifikatov - ta je obdobou kuponovej privatizacie a hodnota
ich bodu suvisi s vekom majitela tohto dokladu.
    Sucasna vlada povazuje za nevyhnutne riesit vyuzitie odpadu
dreva pre vyrobu elektrickej energie, vybudovanie exportneho
pristavu pre vyrobky z celulozy a gulatiny, vystavbu a
rekonstrukciu ciest a vyuzitie geotermalnej energie. Prvy statny
investicny programu bol uz vytvoreny pre obdobie 1995 - 1997.
Kazdy rok sa reviduje s vyhladom na trojrocne obdobie. Len
projekty zaradene do tohto programu sa mozu financovat zo
statneho rozpoctu, alebo z uverov garantovanych vladou. Podla
odhadu Svetovej banky sa zdroje pouzitelne na statne investicie
pohybuju pre obdobie 1995-1977 okolo troch percent hrubeho
domaceho produktu, t.j. okolo 200 milionov lotysskych latosov.
    Medzi SR a Lotysskom neboli zatial uzatvorene dohody o
zamedzeni dvojakeho zdanenia a zabraneni danovemu uniku v odbore
dani z prijmov a majetku a dohoda o podpore a vzajomnej ochrane
investicii. Uzatvorenie tychto zmluv medzi SR a Lotysskom sa
planuje na rok 1997.
    Rober Rom dh ga
    * * *    Stretnutia na vrcholnej urovni este tohto roku v SR    Stretnutia na vrcholnej urovni este tohto roku v SR
   
   Budapest 18. septembra (spravodajca TASR Peter Klenko) -Este
v tomto roku sa na uzemi SR uskutocnia oficialne stretnutia
premierov SR a Madarska, Vladimira Meciara a Gyulu Horna, ako aj
predsedov parlamentov oboch krajin, Ivana Gasparovica a Zoltana
Gala.
    Vyplynulo to zo zaverov dnesneho budapestianskeho rokovania
ministrov zahranicnych veci oboch krajin, Pavla Hamzika a Laszlo
Kovacsa, ktory sucasne informoval aj o dalsich pripravovanych
navstevach ministra obrany SR v Madarsku, madarskeho ministra
kultury a skolstva v SR, ci stretnutiach na urovni parlamentnych
vyborov. Hostitel sucasne pozval ministra zahranicnych veci SR
Pavla Hamzika na oficialnu navstevu Madarskej republiky.
   mst    Pavol Hamzik ukoncil navstevu Madarskej republiky    Pavol Hamzik ukoncil navstevu Madarskej republiky
   
   Budapest 18. septembra (spravodajca TASR Peter Klenko) -Za
velmi otvorene a uzitocne oznacil dnesne rokovania v Budapesti
minister zahranicnych veci SR Pavol Hamzik.
   Ako uviedol na otazku spravodajcu TASR, s madarskym rezortnym
partnerom prerokovali aj aspekty europskej a transatlantickej
integracie. "Madarsky minister zahranicnych veci hovoril v tejto
suvislosti o vzajomnej podpore integracnych snah, ale hovorili
sme aj o tom, ze zakladnym vychodiskom je zaujem madarskej a
slovenskej strany na usporiadani spornych otazok. Nepodliehame
tu ziadnym tlakom, aj ked vieme, ze Europska unia vita akykolvek
pokrok a prehlbenie dovery na obidvoch stranach," povedal
minister zahranicnych veci SR a dodal, ze v suvislosti s
prehlbovanim dovery este je na com pracovat.
   Popri sirokom okruhu otazok bilateralnych vztahov bola
integracia aj predmetom popoludnajsich rozhovorov Pavla Hamzika
s predsedom vlady MR Gyulom Hornom a predsedom budapestianskeho
parlamentu Zoltanom Galom, ktori prijali sefa slovenskej
diplomacie pocas jeho jednodnovej neoficialnej pracovnej
navstevy madarskej metropoly.
   "Mame rovnako ako ine krajiny eminentny zaujem na tom, aby si
Slovaci v zahranici zachovali svoju jazykovu, kulturnu identitu,
povedal minister v reakcii na otazku Ludovych novin o pripadnom
zriadeni uradu pre koordinaciu pomoci zahranicnym Slovakom a
dodal, ze nevylucuje takyto krok po dokladnom premysleni tejto
problematiky. Koncentracia usilia v zaujme jednotneho postupu
voci mensinam a ich podpory je velmi dolezita, dodal.
   "Prisiel som na nastupnu navstevu, obavy som nemal a som
spokojny," uviedol pred navratom do vlasti Pavol Hamzik a dodal,
ze dnesnu navstevu povazuje za dobre vychodisko pre dalsie
kontakty s madarskym kolegom, o ktorych predpoklada, ze budu
caste.
   Po nabitom celodnovom programe minister zahranicnych veci SR
ukoncil pracovnu navstevu madarskej metropoly a odcestoval do
vlasti.
   mst

text: The *HACKED* Labour Party
processed_text: hacked labour party

text:
Policy? What policy? In the run-up to the coming election, all the political parties,
not just Labour, will be publishing their manifestoes, setting
out how they intend to run the country if they get into power.
Issues like unemployment, crime, taxation and Britain in Europe
will be addressed, with each party claiming that their policy
is what the people want and denouncing what the other parties
have published as being the opposite of what the electorate
wants. The simple fact is that the parties will attempt to construct
a manifesto which will garner them the most votes come Election
Day. Labour's proposals for a Windfall Tax on the utilities, and
giving the Lottery franchise to a non-profit organisation are two
examples of minor pieces of policy which are designed to appeal
directly to the man in the street - a kind of a policy soundbite
that candidates can wave at voters like one would entice a dog
with a bone. But the fact is, there are much bigger issues which need to be
addressed, such as our country's economic and social problems, which
are a thousand times more important than whether the National Lottery
is run for profit or not. As we approach the 21st century, Britain is in crisis. Whether we
like to admit it or not, our country faces immense problems, both
social and economic. Socially, we are on a downward spiral - since
World War II, our population has been continually on the increase,
and Britain is now overpopulated. There simply aren't enough jobs
to go around, and so unemployment is on the increase and, with it,
we see the symptoms of a sick society - crime, drugs and vandalism
are rampant and on the increase. Economically, we also face huge problems. Britain joined the Common
Market in order to facilitate trade with our European neighbours,
but now we suddenly find that we're part of a European Union, with
our fellow members attempting to force us to accept federal rule from
Brussels, and a single European currency which would end London's
importance as the world's financial centre. We see France and Germany
dictating to us what we can and cannot do. We see the European Courts
instructing our Government to pay out compensation to the families of
terrorists shot dead while in the process of carrying out a bombing
campaign. We see Germany attempting what it tried in 1914 and again in
1939 - the takeover of Europe, except this time it's doing it through
economic instead of military means. We see French police threatening to
use CS gas on British lorry driver who blockade the roads, whilst standing
idly by while French lorry drivers bring the entire country to a halt. For Pete's sake, let's stop letting Brussels dictate what we can and can't
do. We have a veto - we should use it, instead of allowing Germany to
destroy our economy through their puppets in Brussels. Britain's citizens
have the right to self-determination. It's a right guaranteed under the
United Nations. Let's make sure that we keep that right and that we don't
hand control of our economy and, thus our country, to others. Issues like a Windfall Tax and who runs the Lottery are minor issues - totally
insignificant in the overall picture. Whoever wins the next election will
most likely, lead Britain into the next millenium. We'd like to see how they
plan do deal with the long-term as well as the short-term problems. And the
fact is, that, if the next government is going to solve the long-term problems,
it's going to have to take drastic and unpopular steps in the short-term. The
problem is, of course, that moves like raising taxes aren't election-winners. But surely
the people of Britain are intelligent enough to see that short-term sacrifices
and hardship are necessary for long-term gain. We aren't children, but we do
want our children to grow up in a better world, and if that means that we have
to make sacifices and pay a few extra pence in the pound in order to help the
Government stabilise the economy, reduce unemployment, fix the NHS and provide
better education for our children, then I think that the majority of the electorate
will be prepared to accept those short-term hardships, in order to ensure that,
down the road, Britain will be a straonger nation and a better place to live. The Government is meant to work for the people - All the people;
not just Labour voters or Conservative voters. The various political parties
need to stop being so polarised, and start working together. We are sick and
tired of watching front benchers on both sides of the House trading snide
insults and innuendo with their counterparts on the other side. Instead, why
can't we see a little cooperation? Compromise is a word that doesn't seem to
appear in the political dictionary. What's to stop a Government from
drafting bills and forming Governmental policy in consultation and with
input from the Opposition? That way, we might see some better balanced
legislation and policy that reflects the views of the entire country, instead
of just the majority. We are approaching a point at which Parliamentary reform will become a
necessity. It is no longer necessary to elect representatives to vote on
our behalf in the Parliament - the advent of the information superhighway
will mean that every citizen could vote on legislation from their own home.
Kind of like having a series of referendums, voted on electronically. The
question is, will the politicians be willing to give up their positions of
power and hand over that power to make decisions to the electorate. We've
seen how reluctant the current Government is to allow a referendum on Europe.
But don't be fooled either by the Referendum Party which is effectively James
Goldsmith's own private political party, funded directly from his own coffers,
and espousing his own Anglo-French views. If the Referendum Party attains it's
goals, the first person to benefit will be Goldsmith himself. His business
interests would be greatly served by full integration with Europe. The real
question is, would Britain's? Our basic message to Labour and the other political parties is this: In the
run-up to the upcoming election, let's see some inelligent and responsible
policies put forward, not just short-term pacifiers like tax-cuts which will
have to be paid for somewhere down the road. If sacrifices have to be made in
order to make this country a better place for us all, then let us know. Inform
us. Tell us the pros and cons of various policies. We don't want to see attacks
on other parties' policies - we want to see reasonable, balanced and informative
debate, not blatant attacks. Too many politicians seem to think that saying
something makes it true. From now on, if a politician says that such-and-such
a party's policies are wrong, we want to hear him back up that assertion with
reasonable argument; and "That's not what the people want!" isn't a reasonable
argument, by the way - what the people want will become clear when the votes
are counted. And, hopefully, when they are counted, the Government which results
will be a better and more responsible one than any previous government, whether
Tory or Labour. aohp 96 |

Crackers zijn diegenen die gewoon voor het plezier, of omdat ze enige roem willen verwerven of uit ethische overwegingen (bijvoorbeeld een kinderporno website kraken) een webpagina veranderen. Hetgeen we nu dus gedaan hebben is een voorbeeld van cracken, alhoewel we toch hackers zijn... Onze frustratie is begrijpelijk want wij willen niks anders dan een onderscheid tussen hackers en crackers. Gelukkig zijn er mensen in de politiek, zoals Senator Q bijvoorbeeld, die wel bewust zijn van het probleem en ernaar streven om dit probleem de wereld uit te helpen. Dus dit is infeite een boodschap naar de politici toe, die HEEL ernstig mag opgenomen worden, want we laten het hier niet bij... Greets : securax.org, htwX, nostalg1c, r00t-dude, Zoa Chien, Zymot1c, ... en vele anderen. Link :

    Statement Since 1902, Meredith Corporation has focused on providing our customers
    with products and services that distinguish themselves on the basis of quality, customer
    service and value. Our Online Privacy Policies are designed to help us serve our customers
    while meeting their privacy expectations. We are a member of the Direct Marketing Association (DMA) and Magazine

ohh yeahhh! Crime Boys here.*&%$#@! #$@!&* hmmm... Owned by Crime Boys!! *&!@$# No Brasil a imprensa controla o que o
povo vai ver e escutar, mas agora chegou a vez dos fracos e oprimidos falar. Se você chegou aqui LEIA! Se não ler
é porque aceita o que a imprensa lhe impõe, então não reclame de NADA! HOJE É O DIA DA CAÇA! __________________________________ Argumentos do Governo e imprensa
servil Durante a recente mobilização dos
trabalhadores rurais sem terra, foram veiculados pela imprensa diversos
argumentos do Governo, e outros simplesmente repetidos por colunistas
oficialistas. Vamos a eles. "O MST depreda prédios públicos". O que de fato aconteceu: A rigor,
o prejuízo foi uma porta de vidro no prédio da receita em São Paulo, assumida
publicamente pelos próprios funcionários e inocentando os trabalhadores. Em
nenhum outro prédio público houve qualquer problema; ao contrário, em todos
eles, procuramos limpar e deixar como encontramos. A PF fez perícia no prédio
do INCRA-DF e não encontrou nada fora do lugar. Nossa opinião: E quando o
governo depreda patrimônio público de muito mais valor, aconteceu alguma
coisa? Por exemplo, quantos membros do governo estão presos por corrupção?
Quantos Ministros devolveram aos cofres públicos os gastos com as viagens
realizadas à ilha de Fernando de Noronha, para ir à praia? E o prejuízo que,
somente em 1999, deu ao Banco Central no apoio aos bancos, de R$ 9,7 bilhões de
reais, de quem devemos cobrar? "MST faz reféns e se
equipara à ditadura e aos torturadores". O que aconteceu: não houve
nenhum refém em nenhum prédio público. Refém é quando se prende uma pessoa
em troca de alguma coisa. Nenhum funcionário público ficou preso. Mesmo em
ocasiões anteriores, quando o Ministro fez um levantamento de 575 reféns, fez
uma acusação leviana pois a maioria das ações eram realizadas pelo movimento
sindical. Apenas em oito casos o MST estava envolvido. O caso mais hilariante
aconteceu quando a CONTAG cercou o prédio do INCRA em Pernambuco e o Ministro
logo contabilizou os 200 funcionários que continuaram trabalhando dentro do Prédio,
como reféns. A CNASI, Confederação Nacional das
Associações dos Servidores do INCRA, divulgou uma nota pública dizendo ser
mentira as acusações do ministro. Ora, se fosse verdade que fizemos reféns,
porque ninguém está preso? O governo não perderia a oportunidade de prender
militantes do MST com essa acusação. Nossa opinião: O povo brasileiro
é hoje o verdadeiro refém de um governo insensível e de uma política econômica
que aumenta a pobreza e os problemas sociais de nosso povo. "O MST está radicalizando
suas manifestações". O que aconteceu: O MST realizou
manifestações em todas as capitais do país. Em apenas duas delas houve
incidentes com a Polícia: Paraná e São Paulo. Ora, se nossas ações tivessem
sido violentas, agressivas, a Policia não teria agido também em todos lugares?
No caso do Paraná ficou evidente para toda sociedade quem foram os violentos,
ao proibir que os ônibus chegassem à cidade. E ao atacar com tropa de choque e
com violência desmedida, resultou em mais de cem feridos, um morto e dois
desaparecidos. Nossa opinião: O governo sabe
que há um aumento da mobilização social, como resultado do agravamento da política
econômica que inviabilizou a agricultura e a reforma agrária. A grande
novidade dessa mobilização não foi a radicalidade do MST, mas o fato de que
diversos outros movimentos realizaram atos de protesto, e contundentes. Assim, o
movimento sindical, dos trabalhadores rurais, interrompeu a rodovia que liga o
centro-oeste ao país, em Rondonópolis. A Federação dos Trabalhadores do Pará,
interrompeu a Transamazônica, e ocupou o BASA em Belém. O MPA (Movimento dos
Pequenos Agricultores) ocupou a parte da frente do Banco Central, em porto
Alegre. O MAB (Movimento dos Atingidos por Barragens), ocupou a sede da empresa
Gerasul (eletrosul privatizada), a CPT (Comissão Pastoral da Terra) ocupou o
INCRA da Paraíba. "O MST fere o Estado de
Direito". O que aconteceu: O MST fez
mobilizações em frente aos prédios, ocupou o andar térreo, manifestou-se. Até
um representante do Banco Mundial, presente no BNDES admitiu que isso é normal
nos Estados Unidos. Aonde está o direito de manifestar-se? Só pode
manifestar-se a favor do governo? Nossa opinião: E quando o
governo fere a Lei, como no caso do salário mínimo, ou no acordo com o FMI,
que se quer foi aprovado pelo Senado, ou ainda as medidas provisórias ou relatórios
da CPI ? E quem cobra do governo que não está aplicando a lei, das desapropriações?
Aqui cabe lembrar a máxima de Getúlio Vargas: "Aos amigos tudo, aos
inimigos a Lei" "O MST está isolado da
sociedade". O que aconteceu: O MST tem
diversas formas de receber apoio da sociedade. Tanto da população comum, que
sustenta nossos acampamentos, nossas marchas, que nos saúda na rua, como através
das organizações da sociedade. Como estamos isolados, se durante todo tempo
estivemos com apoio da OAB, da CNBB, e de todas entidades dos trabalhadores?
Recebemos solidariedade até da Força Sindical. Mesmo em termos de pesquisas de
opinião pública, o Movimento tem apoio de 56%, que é maior do que o apoio ao
Poder Judiciário, da Polícia. Na semana passada recebemos o título de cidadão
honorário de Brasília, enquanto o mesmo título era negado ao senador ACM
(PFL-BA). Quando entramos na cidade, nós percebemos se a sociedade nos rejeita
ou nos apóia, vocês acham que seríamos estúpidos o suficiente para fazer
pressão contra o governo se a sociedade nos rejeitasse? Nossa opinião: O verdadeiro
isolado da sociedade brasileira é o governo, que gasta milhões em propaganda,
em mentiras, e não consegue sair de 14% de apoio do povo brasileiro. Basta ler
os jornais e ver as manifestações de juristas, CNBB, políticos, a favor da
reforma agrária e contra o Governo. Mesmo nos episódios recentes, a maioria
dos governadores nos recebeu, e de certa forma, nos apoiou. Até o governador Mário
Covas se solidarizou. "O PT está contra o MST". O que aconteceu: A imprensa
buscou criar um clima de que alguns deputados desaprovavam ações violentas, e
portanto desaprovavam o MS. Ora o MST também é contra ações violentas, e
também somos contra depredar prédio público. Na verdade tratou-se de uma
artimanha de imprensa, para tentar passar a imagem de divisão e que o MST
estava isolado até de seus aliados históricos. Ora, o PT e os demais partidos
de oposição sempre estiveram conosco, e também nessa jornada. O massacre do
Paraná somente não se transformou no Carajás do Sul, porque durante todo
tempo tivemos a presença dos deputados do PT em todos momentos, na manifestação
e depois. O senador Suplicy esteve conosco no Paraná e teve um papel
importante, igualmente o presidente da comissão de direitos humanos, Deputado
Marcos Rolim, para identificar o assassino dentro da PM. Recebemos apoio
parlamentar, do partido, e de suas principais lideranças. Nossa opinião: O governo quis
afastar os partidos da questão, para evitar de  politizá-la, mas o efeito
foi o contrário, os partidos de oposição se sentiram provocados e aumentaram
ainda mais a presença e a solidariedade. "O Governo FHC foi o que mais
desapropriou". A propaganda do governo repetia de que o
governo FHC foi o que mais fez. E evidentemente que, comparando-se aos regimes
militares que nada fizeram, ele fez mais. Mas usar expressões como duas Bélgica
etc. é no mínimo, manipulação. Basta lembrar que foi também no governo FHC
que o empresário CR Almeida, de Curitiba, adquiriu 4 milhões de terras públicas
no Pará, que equivale a uma Dinamarca. Ou que durante o governo FHC , mais de
400 mil famílias de pequenos agricultores perderam suas propriedades e outros 2
milhões de assalariados perderam o emprego na agricultura. O governo fantasia os números
engordando-os com regularização de posse das regiões Norte e Centro-Oeste.
Estatisticamente, os dados aparecem, mas o problema social, real da falta de
assentamentos continua. O Governo diz que assentou 80 mil apenas em 1999,mas as
tabelas oficiais  do INCRA revelam que foram apenas 25 mil famílias em
terras desapropriadas. "O MST queria cadáveres". Com freqüência o governo planta notícias
de que o MST quer cadáveres. Ora, isso é no mínimo, um desrespeito a inteligência,
como se alguém de sã consciência usasse a tática de provocar mortes, para se
mostrar como vítima. O MST já tem vítimas de sobra. Pior foi a ameaça do
presidente de que a morte do companheiro do Paraná deveria servir de alerta.
Alerta de que? Que haveriam mais mortes? De que elas continuam impunes? "O MST goza de total
impunidade". O que aconteceu: Desde a
redemocratização do país (1985-1999) foram assassinados no campo 1.169 
(mil cento de sessenta e nove) pessoas, entre lideranças de trabalhadores,
religiosos, sindicalistas, advogados dos trabalhadores e até dois deputados.
Destes, apenas 58 foram a julgamento, os demais estão totalmente impunes, sem
sequer ter processo. Dos 58, apenas 11 foram condenados culpados; 47 foram
inocentados apesar das provas. Dos onze, apenas três estão presos, os demais
estão foragidos. Apenas dos três casos mais famosos como: Chico Mendes, Padre
Josimo e o Sindicalista João Canuto. Nossa opinião: Quem de fato goza
de impunidade nesse país? Quem está preso, daquelas inúmeras denúncias de
superfaturamento nas desapropriações do INCRA ? Quem está preso das denúncias
de empresas que contrataram construção em assentamentos superfaturados? Quem
está preso daqueles casos de corrupção do banco da terra, que as entidades do
Fórum Nacional denunciaram na Procuradoria Geral da República? Os jornais
noticiaram que 96% da área indígena dos Pataxós da Bahia, está invadida por
fazendeiros. E que a lei determina que sejam expulsos e as terras retornem para
os Pataxós. Alguém tem notícia de algum despejo ? "O interlocutor é o Jungmann,
não precisa da área econômica". O Ministro da Reforma Agrária deveria
dar graça as Deus que pressionamos. Vejam a evolução do orçamento do INCRA:
96: l,6 bilhões, 97: 1,8 bilhões, 98: 2,2 bilhões, 99: 1,2 bilhões e para
2000: 1,3 bilhões. Todos funcionários do INCRA sabem que a fazenda cortou o orçamento
do orgão em 99 e 2000 e inviabilizou a reforma agrária. Os funcionários do
setor de planejamento enviaram uma proposta da necessidade de 2,4 bilhões para
assentar cem mil famílias. E isso foi cortado  para 1,3 bilhões. ATOS FALHOS DO
GOVERNO Regime democrático precisa usar exército
contra seu povo ? O Governo ameaçou o MST com exército
para desocupar prédios. E recentemente utilizou o exército para proteger sua
fazenda particular. Nesta fazenda, FHC possui um sócio (e portanto, o exército
ajudou a proteger), o seu Mineiro, grileiro no Pontal do Paranapanema. Sua
fazenda Santa Maria, foi grilada por seu sogro, ex-governador Sodré, de terras
públicas. Jungmann afirma que sem terra não
foi assassinado Nem haviam iniciado as investigações
do assassinato do sem-terra no Paraná e o Ministro Jungmann se apressou a
repetir em Brasília, a propaganda do Governador do Paraná, afirmando que o sem
terra não tinha sido morto no local do conflito. Em 24 horas de investigações
do deputado da comissão de Direitos Humanos, Marcos Rolim, junto a PM do Paraná,
constatou não só o local, a hora, como a viatura aonde estava o soldado que
desferiu o tiro. Governo censura entrevista de Stedile
na TV Cultura Não se tratava de um governo democrático
que respeita a Lei. Ora, o governo determinou, através do Ministro das comunicações, Andréa Matarazzo, que a
entrevista ao vivo não poderia, e de fato não foi veiculado nas TVs
Educativas, onde o governo federal tem influência. Felizmente a TV Cultura de
SP, RS e Minas não se dobraram e passaram a entrevista, mas nos demais estados
vigorou a democracia. Só pode falar bem do governo. O QUE O MST QUERIA DE
FATO, QUAIS ERAM NOSSAS REINVIDICAÇÕES - O MST apresentou uma pauta de
reivindicações no Palácio do Planalto, e nos Ministérios, que se resume a: - Que o governo acelere a desapropriação
de latifúndios improdutivos, para assentar todas as famílias que estão
acampadas. Ou seja, pedimos que aplique o artigo 189 da Constituição
Brasileira. - Pedimos que o governo coloque recursos
necessários para o INCRA funcionar. Ou seja pedimos dinheiro pro próprio
governo. - Pedimos que o crédito de custeio
passe de 1.500 reais por família para 3 mil reais, o que é insignificante. - Pedimos que o crédito de investimento
passe de 7.500 reais para 20 mil por família. (Um trator custa 70 mil reais!) - Pedimos que o governo libere recursos
para instalar agroindústrias em forma de cooperativa. - Pedimos que o crédito para construir
uma casa para a família, passe dos atuais 2.500 (!!) para 4.500 reais. Quanto
as elites retiram na Caixa Econômica Federal para construir suas casas?
Honestamente, alguém de sã consciência considera essas propostas revolucionárias,
atentado ao direito a propriedade, atentado ao regime democrático, uma afronta
ao governo? AS MEDIDAS DO GOVERNO Como o governo não quis atender o MST e
as famílias assentadas e acampadas, resolve satanizá-lo, criou um bode expiatório,
para o isolamento que o governo sofre, assustou-se com sua própria
impopularidade e baixou as seguintes medidas: Criou uma divisão especial na Policia
Federal para cuidar de sem terra Na prática é a refundação do DOPS.
Teria a Polícia Federal tanto tempo a ter com sem terras, com as denúncias das
CPIs? O governo está, na verdade, criminalizando a reforma agrária como um
todo? ITR nos Estados O ITR é uma disposição constitucional
prerrogativa do governo federal. Portanto  precisa mudar a constituição.
Mesmo que o governo mude a constituição, como é imposto ele seria votado
apenas em ‘200l e aí as assembléias estaduais refariam as leis de
cada estado, e seria cobrado, provavelmente em 2002, e por tanto recolhido
apenas em 2003, quando esse governo já vai estar de pijamas. O ITR só pode ser
eficaz se o governo, tiver vontade política de cobrar e se juntar as informações
com o Imposto de Renda e com as informações de patrimônio. No governo
Carvalho Pinto, o ITR era estadual em São Paulo e foi inócuo. Descentralizar as obras de
assentamentos para os governos estaduais Isso depende de acordo político, será
que o governo federal perguntou se os governos estaduais querem aceitar o
abacaxi de assumir, sem recursos, apenas os encargos da reforma agrária e a
pressão social? Área ocupada não será
desapropriada Primeiro é um blefe porque já existe
um decreto de 1997 que trata disso e foi completamente ineficaz. Ora, se uma
determinada fazenda ocupada não for desapropriada, bastaria o movimento acampar
na frente, ao lado, atrás, e indicar aquela área. Na prática, repete o que a
Coroa fez no império. Todo escravo que fugisse das senzalas, não teria direito
a liberdade. Direção Nacional do MST Movimento dos Tralhadores Rurais Sem Terra __________________________________ "O primeiro homem que inventou de
cercar uma parcela de terra e dizer "isto é meu", e encontrou gente

text:
anonce001 Message
important de Claude (Propriétaire ) Bonjour, Je m'appelle Claude morin, propriétaire du studio
magic. Tatatouage Je vous annonce que le studio fermera ses portes définitivements le 31 décembre 2000 pour
les raisons qui suit... Il y a maintenant 8 ans que je suis ouvert à l'ancan larose. Lorsque j'ai débuté, le commerce n'était pas ce qu'il est aujourd'hui. Le tatouage
n'était pas aussi populaire dans l'Outaouais. Si le tatouage connais
cette popularité, c'est un peu à cause de moi. J'étais le premier studio à
faire de la publicité, dans les journeaux,
annonces populaires et ensuite cktf. De plus en plus de studios
de tatouages ouvrent leur porte, donc une compétion
très féroce ! Je n'ai plus la force pour concurencer avec eux, ca
pouce comme des champignons. Il y a une bonne chose
dans tout ça, il y aura de moins en moins de tatouage
maison. Appellon cela du tatouage à risque. Les
aiguilles ne sont pas toujours adéquates, ils utilises des cordes de guitard pour fabriquer des aiguilles à tattoo. Souvent, la stérilisation n'est pas apropriée non plus.
S"il y avait moins de tatoueur maison, les risques de maladies diminuraient.
Lorque vous serez près pour un tattoo, prenez votre temps, visiter les studios,poser des questions, examiner
les lieux et le tatoueur. Si vous ne vous sentez pas
allaise, allez ailleur. Même s"il baisse son prix, la santé n'a
pas de prix. Les aiguilles doivent être jeter après usage. Ma
seconde raison de fermer est que, je n'est plus de
vie familliale.Je suis 90% du temps
à mon commerce. Je ne vois ni ma fille grandir
ni ma famille. Ils me manquent et nos journées de
congés ne coincide jamais. Depuis 8 ans, je n'est pris aucune vacance. Il y a quelques années, j'adorais mon métier.
J'aimais tatouer, et mes clients me sont très chers. l'accomplisement, le respect
et le contact mon permis de remplir mon réfrigérateur. J'ai même développé une certaine amitier
avec mes clients. Ces pourquoi j'ai
donc décidé d'aviser tous mes clients
et ami(es) de la fermeture de mon studio. Maintenant
mes priorité dans l'avenir son
ma fille ma mère et ma santé. De plus, ma
mère est veuve depuis l'ans passé. Elles ont besoin de moi
et j'ai besoin d'elles. Le son d'une cloche m'a fait réaliser que je négligais les
deux personne que j'aime le plus au monde. De plus,
ma santé mental et physique ont besoin de repos. A force
d'acumuler des situations négatives comme problèmes, des tracas
et des évènements tristes, le côté mental
en mange un coup. Certains appellerait ça un burn out, d'autre dépression. Moi j'appelle ça ( give me a break ). Avant de finir comme mon chanteur favori, (Dédé Fortin des
Coloc) je préfère me retirer dignement
et la tête haute. Je laisse la place à la concurence et de grace:
respectez vos clients, se
sont des êtres humains peu importe la
langue ou la nationalité. Mario Lirette, enciennement de CKTF et le sympatique Julien Tremblay, sont venu animer le
party d'annivarsaire de mon studio.Je me rappellerai toujours de la question que Mario m'a
posé et qui m'a fait refléchir. J'ai
eu la chance de les tatouer, de rire des blagues
de Mario
et d'entendre Julien à la guitard nous faire toute une performance
que seul lui, c'est le
faire. Après nous sommes aller
souper à la brasserie de l'Encan Larose. Les patron
ont offert le souper à toute l'équipe de CKTF, ainsi qu'à mon
équipe. Assi devant Mario, on
a pri une bière,
on a bavardé et c'est là que Mario me demanda
si j'aimais mon travail. Je lui est
répondu que oui. Il m'a dit " travail parce que t'aime ton  travail, pas pour
devenir riche". A ce moment,  j'ai compris que lorsque j'ai débuté, j'adorais
mon travail. Je
n'avais pas boucoup de client  mais j'aimais faire
se travail. Après quelques
annonces, la clientelle
grandissait, donc beaucoup plus d'argent. De là,
je me suis mis
à aimer l'argent et en
suite je n'avais plus de temps
pour apprécier mon
travail et son art. Ce que je voulais,
c'était de grandir
pour en faire toujours plus.
J'ai réussi, mais mon
travail ma volé ma fille, ma mêre et ma santé. Maintenant,
je me rend
contre que j'avais la gloire mais
pas plus d'argent
dans mes poches. J'ai négligé
les êtres que j'aime le plus au monde. Maintenant j'aimerais faire quelques salutations et remerciments à tous mes bons amis et fidèles clients. Mes ami(es) qui ont su me faire confiance et m'encourager pendant toutes ces années. Je tiens à saluer Marie-Eve Emond et Karine Cadieux, mes 2 ex-assistantes, de retour à la brasserie de l'Encan et la petite
nouvelle karine Poirier. Je ne peux passer à côté de
la gang de cktf. Il y a Martin
Grenier qui m'a invité en onde pour le tatouer sur son émission retour juste pour le fun. Chapeau pour
ton émission, j'ai adoré l'expérience.
"Martin, vous avez du cran toi et Michel." Jaimerais salué
tes deux beaux
enfants, Maxime et Amélie, ainsi que ton épouse Johane. Elle n'est j'amais venue se faire tatouer, elle avais trop peur. Ça sera pour une autre foi. Il y a aussi Eric Gagnon et sa blonde.         As women and children left the village they were met by the Zionist army

        attack after the surrender that killed several Israeli soldiers, 80-100

text:
personal cd players, stereos and mini systems About Aiwa | | | | | | About Aiwa | | Aiwa is the leading audio entertainment brand in the UK because it provides high quality products at affordable prices. How has this been achieved? The quest for sensible innovation Since 1951 Aiwa has specialised in high quality audio products, continually developing and introducing new technologies to business and consumer markets throughout the world. Today, Aiwa places even more importance on performance, quality and innovation, and invests an unusually high proportion of sales income to research & development. This continuous investment means that Aiwa customers, in turn, continue to enjoy benefits that match their lifestyles. Recent examples are valuable features such as anti-shock personal CD players for sports and fitness enthusiasts and the award-winning anti-theft device integrated in many VCRs to reduce crime. Pioneers of modern business efficiency To ensure and maintain high levels of customer satisfaction, Aiwa has lead the industry in the introduction of new manufacturing and process systems, together with innovative management techniques aimed at reducing costs as well as improving quality. It is this crucial combination of high quality and lower cost which differentiates Aiwa from the majority of its competitors. Quite simply, it results in better value for money . Retaining quality whilst reducing cost The concept of value for money lies at the heart of Aiwa's success: it was one of the first Japanese companies to recognise that product quality must be maintained at the expense of company overheads. Long before most other Japanese corporations, for example, Aiwa determined to increase its manufacturing operations in territories where costs are lower. The decision to reduce operations in Japan was a brave but enlightened one, and the resulting, often quite dramatic, savings were immediately passed on to customers. Today, around 90% of all Aiwa products are made outside Japan with increasingly local sourcing of parts and materials. Just one example of this policy was the establishment of a significant manufacturing facility in Gwent, South Wales as early as 1980.
Aiwa has also pioneered new developments in logistics to maintain the pressure on costs. Components move smoothly and efficiently from suppliers through assembly, enabling finished products to reach retailers promptly by eliminating expensive delays. Meeting the challenge Customers demand quality - a stimulating but rewarding challenge which Aiwa relishes as it continually identifies and implements new ways to provide greater quality at lower cost. Aiwa (UK) Ltd. Environmental Policy Aiwa (UK) Ltd. is committed to establishing and reviewing it's significant impacts on the Environment and the continual review and improvement of it's environmental performance including the prevention of pollution where applicable. Aiwa (UK) Ltd. will take into account all relevant Environment Legislation and Regulations during this process. Aiwa (UK) Ltd. will comply with those Environmental Standards as set out in BS EN ISO 14001: 1996 The responsibility for implementing this policy lies with all employees of Aiwa (UK) Ltd. and as such will be readily available to them. Suitable training to raise awareness and promote active participation will be provided for all employees. The policy will be communicated to all suppliers as part of the Contract Review Process and will be taken into account when determining "Preferred Suppliers". Address Aiwa (UK) Ltd Unit 5, Heathrow Summit Centre Skyport Drive West Drayton Middlesex UB7 0LY

text: r0b1n h00d slu7 strikes again! Good afternoon.  I'm Al Gore , and I'd like to tell you about myself. I know a lot about hardship, because I came into this world as a poor black child in a tiny town in the backwoods of Tennessee.  I was born in a log cabin that I built with my own hands. I taught myself to read by candlelight and helped support my 16 brothers and sisters by working summers as a deck hand on a Mississippi River steamboat. My mother taught me the value of education, so every day, I would walk 5 miles to a one-room schoolhouse.  I was a mischievous, fun loving scamp, thought I never dreamed that one day, my youthful escapades would serve as the inspiration for "Huckleberry Finn." Back then, black folks in the south were second-class citizens. One day, a  traveling minister came through town, and I asked him if anyone was ever going to do something to guarantee civil rights for all Americans. Well, I guess I made an impression. You see, the minister's name was Martin Luther King, Jr. My father was a United States Senator. He once perched me on his knee and said, "Son, if you work hard and listen to your mama, someday you can live in a hotel in Washington, D.C., and go to an exclusive prep school." But life of privilege was not for me. After getting my high school diploma, I took a job in a hot, dirty textile mill.  I was so appalled at the treatment of the workers there that I organized a union. Later,that experience inspired a movie - which is why, to this day, my close friends at the AFL-CIO call me "Norma Rae." When word got out what an 18 year old factory worker had done, Harvard called and offered me a scholarship.  I captained the hockey team to four consecutive national championships, but I also played football and was good enough to win the Heisman Trophy.  During my college years, I lived in a  housing project and moonlighted playing lead guitar for a little rockband. You may have heard of it -- the Rolling Stones. But there was a war going on, and I felt I had to serve my country. So I enlisted in the U. S. Army and went to Vietnam.  I was deeply opposed to the war, but I did my duty as a soldier and came back home with the Medal of Honor and the Croix de Guerre. When I got back, I took a long journey across this great land of ours. I've crossed the deserts bare, man, I've breathed the mountain air, man, I've traveled, I've done my share, man, I've been everywhere. And the people I met at truckstops and campgrounds and homeless shelters on that journey all said the same thing: "Al, we need you in Washington." I knew they were right, but first I had to take care of some other business---building the World Trade Center, founding the Audubon Society, doing the clinical research that proved smoking caused cancer, and coming up with the recipe for Mrs. Field's chocolate chip cookies. Finally, I deferred to the demands of the people of Tennessee and allowed them to elect me to the House of Representatives and the Senate. And then one winter day nearly nine years ago, for no particular reason, I answered the call of the people once again and took the oath of office as Vice President of the United States. thieves like us this hack has not been sanctioned by a political party or candidate. welcome to one of the former main webpages of the gop. take a minute to read: As my dear friend Thomas Paine once said, these *are* the times
that try mens' souls. We're faced with the realization that the united
states government was never meant to scale to the level at which it
currently sits. It seems hard to believe that those distinguished
gentlemen, sitting back in that dusty hall in Philadelphia, ever imagined
a nation as large and as populous as our own. Indeed, Jefferson himself
faced the first indicator of this woeful inability to scale when faced
with the Louisiana Purchase. It came down to this great man, who had
crafted so much, that for all their wisdom and caring and structure, they
had made a country in which there were no rules set for expansion. And
ever since, this maxim, this lack of foresight in men so far sighted, has
throttled and crushed this nation in so many different ways. 
	George W. Bush would make a great president for those states which
traffic not so much in deceny but bigotry. Not acceptance but hate. Not
love but fear. There is no sense of human camaraderie amongst those who
live south of the Mason-Dixon line. At least, no camaraderie for those
whose appearance is not completely and utterly similar to one's own self. 
	So gays, blacks, latinos, and even women, (once they've been
knocked up and sent into a nine month hibernation until they can produce a
male heir,) are treated as less than human. They're not even given the
3/5ths that slaves once were. Their manifest destiny is serving that great
tyrant, the straight white male. 
	And don't presume that I'm unaware of how cliche that may sound.
But sometimes, lord, sometimes cliches prove to be a great truth. And
there is no greater truth in American than the straight white male's
dominance and his Aesopian desire to keep it. I myself seem to be the very
same thing as all the other swine who run this country. For a guy like me,
a vote for Bush is like a vote for continued prosperity. 
	But as the scum also rises, so the sun also sets. 
	I can not conscience vote for Bush. A vote for Bush is a vote
for myself. A vote for Bush is a vote for myself at the expense of
everyone else living in this strange and savage land. For whatever reason,
be it upbringing, my parents, or perhaps even brain damage, I reject the
idea of voting simply for myself. A vote should be cast not simply on
personal issues, but on one's feeling on how your vote will affect the
whole country. 
	Voting for Bush would be voting for myself and voting against
anyone not like me. We don't need to talk about the supreme court, or Al
Gore's endless babbling about that tax cut for the top 1%, because like
your fuzzy mathed lockboxes, it's seared into the American
consciousness. I don't need give you reasons. If you can not see them
yourself, then nothing will ever remove the blinders. 
	Gore isn't the best of men, but I refuse to be stuck in the same
arrested adolesence as all of America's luxury classed celebrities, who
presume that you can only vote for a candidate if his views tally 100%
with your own. That is the folly of the spoiled. Nor can I pretend that
the differences between Gore & Bush are unpronounced. If you believe that,
then Bush has played you as he wanted to play you. He's run as a moderate
Democrat on Democrat issues. It amazes me that all you woeful cynics of
the political process who don't buy the hype have bought the hype so
deeply. 
	Bush is a man whose entire life has been spent in the shadow of a
superior father, and remembering back to those awful days of 1988-1992,
it's hard to imagine Sr. being very superior to anyone, but Dubbya has
used the Senior as his prototype. He's the classic Oedipal, even if that
does mean we must consider the horrific possibility of School Marm Barb
having sex with either George. He's spent his entire life trying to please
his dorky father, and once he gets in office, do you think that's going to
change? He'll mirror Papa's policies as quickly as hate crimes legislation
can be shot down. 
	Again, Gore ain't the best of men, but he's a good man, and he's a
smart man. He may very well be smarter than any man who has ever been
President. He's a fascinating intellect, and while he's a little to the
right of where I wish he'd be, at least he truly understands governmental
compassion, rather than giving it the thin lipped service of W. 
	This election won't affect me in any way. Either way, I'm going to
float to the top. However, I comprehend the effects of my vote on the rest
of the populace, and can not be irresponsible with it. I must vote, as
dear self-aggrandizing Ralph Nader & his chorus of increasingly
irrelevant celebrities have said, "my conscience". My conscience tells me
that I shouldn't fuck over people over for my own self, nor should I
maintain some lofty ideal of a true progressive movement when that
self-same progressive movement can't attract any minorities or gays, and
serves as the political equivalent of a country club for the spoiled and
overpriviledged. 
	As such, I must vote Gore, and I urge you to do so. want more? if you want more dry, shiny, dead republican drivel,
go to http://www.gop.com or http://www.gop.net, or turn on your nearest
television.

text: Seafood Technology Program Seafood Technology Program The Sheldon Jackson College Seafood Technology Program is designed to prepare students for immediate employment in the seafood industry as well as to pursue further education in the field of food technology. Courses have been developed to accommodate industry members by avoiding the two largest fishing seasons, salmon season (June through August) and Pollock A Season (January through March). Classes do not follow the SJC semester format but are held in short one-credit segments of three days, one week or two weeks often using evenings and weekends. Required courses are relevant industry-wide and were developed using input from industry members. Elective courses will be offered to address the interest of students and needs of industry members. Instructors are chosen for their expertise in the field and include members of the University of Alaska Fairbanks Marine Advisory Program, the seafood processing industry and other universities. Full time students are eligible for financial aid packages. All required courses are also approved for JTPA funding. The program is supported through a grant from Arctic Storm, Inc. and Glacier Seafood. For more information call 907-747-2554 or e-mail , the Director of the Seafood Technology Program. Additional information may be found at the .

Welcome to Bray.ie! Fáilte 
          roimh go mBre- Welcome to Bray.ie AN 
          INTRODUCTION TO BRAY by Adrienne 
          Palmer Bray, 
          known as the Gateway to the Garden of Ireland, is now the eighth largest 
          town in Ireland with a population well in excess of 27,000 and is positioned 
          in north east Wicklow, just south of Dublin. Tourism has always been associated with Bray, which is the longest established 
          seaside town in the country. The outbreak of World War 2 put the industry 
          'on hold' for its duration. However, during the 1950s tourists from 
          England, Scotland and Northern Ireland returned to Bray in great numbers 
          to escape the austerity of rationing. Today, Bray is a vibrant holiday resort and boasts fine hotels and guest 
          house accommodation, shops, restaurants and evening entertainment. Available 
          in the immediate locality are fourteen 18-hole golf courses, tennis, 
          fishing, sailing and horse-riding. Other features of Bray are the amusement and games centre. There is 
          also a Leisure centre on Quinsboro road, and a National Sealife Centre 
          on Strand Road. Published

            world's biggest wind farm on the Arklow banks along the county Wicklow 
            coastline. Sports 
              News Bray 
            is Back as Wanderers Beat Kilkenny City Bray 
            Wanders ended a six-game winless streak at the Carlisle grounds - 
            and prevented a drop to the regulation zone- with a 3-0 win over Kilkenny 
            City in the Eircom League Premier Division. Feedback Please

text:
New Page 4 Sobre Secretaria da Saúde do Estado da Paraíba Endereço: Av. Dom Pedro II, n.º 1826 Bairro da Torre João Pessoa - Paraíba CEP: 58.040-440 Fone: (0 ** 83) 241 - 1718 Fax: (0 ** 83) 241 - 1922 E-mail: Missão da
      SES-PB A Secretaria de Estado da Saúde é a instância
    gestora do Sistema Único de Saúde (SUS), no âmbito estadual. Tem como missão promover
    a harmonização e integração dos sistemas municipais de saúde, propiciando condições
    para que possam assumir a gestão da atenção integral à saúde de seus munícipes. Dessa forma, apresenta-se como esfera coordenadora das políticas
    públicas de saúde, no espaço estadual, comprometida com o fortalecimento e a
    consolidação do SUS. Objetivos Institucionais: Condução da política de saúde no âmbito estadual; Desenvolvimento de ações de planejamento, acompanhamento, controle e avaliação; Desenvolvimento e apropriação da ciência e tecnologia, as quais deverão ser
        compartilhadas com as demais instâncias de gestão; Coordenação de programação negociada entre gestores e integrada com os municípios e
        o governo federal; Investimento no desenvolvimento de política de recursos humanos; Execução de serviços e programas estratégicos de competência estadual; Regulação e exercício das relações entre setor público e sociedade civil; Cooperação técnica com os municípios; Uso da inteligência epidemiológica como norteadora das ações e atividades inerentes
        à identificação e intervenção sobre os problemas de saúde; Fortalecimento das instâncias de controle social; Formulação de uma nova política de informação, comunicação e educação em saúde
        que seja coerente com as diretrizes do SUS; Estímulo à capacidade de planejamento e gestão, objetivando o fortalecimento do
        processo de descentralização/municipalização. Projetos Estratégicos: Habilitação de todos os  municípios paraibanos (223) a uma das
        condições de gestão previstas na NOB-SUS 01/96; Reorganização da Atenção Básica de Saúde e manutenção do Pacto de Indicadores de Atenção à Saúde; Implantação e implementação da Rede Estadual de Informações em
          Saúde - REIS-PB - articulada à Rede Nacional de Informações em
          Saúde - RNIS; Consolidação do  PACS/PSF, enquanto estratégia estruturante
          do novo modelo de atenção a saúde; Expansão da  rede de Consórcios Intermunicipais de Saúde; Construção de uma política de sangue e hemoderivados

We just have out pattern don't we? Don't we like it, to know that the grocery has Coke AND Pepsi? And don't we have a habit of still looking around in the grocery store although we already know exactly what we want from last time? Our habits are everywhere. We eat lunch between twelve and two. We have dinner past five. Cars drive and it's not usual for them to be broken
        right? Shouldn't we be glad then that we're bored or the opposite: have too much to do? Because
        something's probably wrong if it isn't. I just thought I'd share that with you guys. "I get knocked down, like I

text: Home Page "The Hacker" Another one got caught today, it's all over the papers. "Teenager Arrested in Computer Crime Scandal", "Hacker Arrested after Bank Tampering"... Damn kids. They're all alike. But did you, in your three-piece psychology and 1950's technobrain, ever take a look behind the eyes of the hacker? Did you ever wonder what made him tick, what forces shaped him, what may have molded him? I am a hacker, enter my world... Mine is a world that begins with school... I'm smarter than most of the other kids, this crap they teach us bores me... Damn underachiever. They're all alike. I'm in junior high or high school. I've listened to teachers explain for the fifteenth time how to reduce a fraction. I understand it. "No, Ms. Smith, I didn't show my work. I did it in my head..." Damn kids id. Probably copied it. They're all alike. I made a discovery today. I found a computer. Wait a second, this is cool. It does what I want it to. If it makes a mistake, it's because I screwed it up. Not because it doesn't like me... Or feels threatened by me... Or thinks I'm a smart ass... Or doesn't like teaching and shouldn't be here... Damn kid. All he does is play games. They're all alike. And then it happened... a door opened to a world... rushing through the phone line like heroin through an addict's veins, an electronic pulse is sent out, a refuge from the day-to-day incompetencies is sought... a board is found. "This is it... this is where I belong..." I know everyone here... even if I've never met them, never talked to them, may never hear from them again... I know you all... Damn kid. Tying up the phone line again. They're all alike... You bet your ass we're all alike... we've been spoon-fed baby food at school when we hungered for steak... the bits of meat that you did let slip through were pre-chewed and tasteless. We've been dominated by sadists, or ignored by the apathetic. The few that had something to teach found us willing pupils, but those few are like drops of water in the desert. This is our world now... the world of the electron and the switch, the beauty of the baud. We make use of a service already existing without paying for what could be dirt-cheap if it wasn't run by profiteering gluttons, and you call us criminals. We explore... and you call us criminals. We seek after knowledge... and you call us criminals. We exist without skin color, without nationality, without religious bias... and you call us criminals. You build atomic bombs, you wage wars, you murder, cheat, and lie to us and try to make us believe it's for our own good, yet we're the criminals. Yes, I am a criminal. My crime is that of curiosity. My crime is that of judging people by what they say and think, not what they look like. My crime is that of outsmarting you, something that you will never forgive me for. I am a hacker, and this is my manifesto. You may stop this individual, but you can't stop us all... after all, we're all alike. H cked by Nightmare®
